docker is best on linux than windows and mac

🧨 Docker Disadvantages
1️⃣ OS Dependency
Linux containers need Linux kernel.
You cannot run Windows container on Linux easily.
(Except using special modes)

2️⃣ Less Isolation Than VM
VM:
Strong isolation
Separate kernel

Container:
Shares kernel

Kernel vulnerability affects all containers

3️⃣ Not Ideal For Different OS Testing

VM can run:
Linux on Windows
Windows on Linux

Different kernel versions
Docker cannot change kernel.

🏗️ When To Use What?
Use Case	               Docker    	VM
Microservices             ✅	      ❌
CI/CD pipelines	          ✅	      ❌
Full OS testing	          ❌     	  ✅
Strong isolation/security	⚠️	      ✅
Lightweight deployment	  ✅	      ❌

🎯Docker uses OS-level virtualization, meaning containers share the host’s kernel and isolate only the application layer. 
In contrast, virtual machines use hardware-level virtualization, where each VM contains a full guest OS and kernel. 
Because Docker does not need to boot a full OS, it is lightweight, faster, and smaller in size.
However, Docker is dependent on the host kernel, while VMs provide stronger isolation and cross-OS compatibility.

🔥
